## 4) AI Agent Workflow (Dynamic)

### Workflow Description

- **Goal:** turn patient intent into safe, useful next actions.
- **Trigger:** patient request or system event (e.g., `VisitCompleted`, schedule opening).
- **Output:** recommendations, notifications, summaries, and full decision trace logs.

### Decision Points

```text
Decision Flow
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ D1: Intent + urgency classification
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Route to self-service scheduling or escalation path
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ D2: Provider/slot recommendation strategy
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Rank by rules, continuity, proximity, preference
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ D3: Reminder/notification strategy
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Send timing and channel based on consent + context
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ D4: Post-visit follow-up strategy
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Monitor future schedules and trigger booking prompts
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ D5: Human handoff decision
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Escalate when confidence/risk thresholds fail
```

### Human-in-the-Loop Moments

- Provider reviews AI summary before clinical use.
- Staff resolves schedule conflicts and complex exceptions.
- High-risk outputs are escalated for manual review.
- Compliance team audits sampled AI traces and incidents.

### Failure Strategy Nodes

```text
Failure Handling
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Missing data
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Request required fields
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Use conservative fallback recommendations
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ External API outage
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Retry with backoff
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Switch to backup integration if available
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Notify patient with fallback path
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Scheduling conflict
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Re-query slot inventory
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Offer nearest valid alternatives
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Low AI confidence
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Block autonomous action
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Route to human queue
```

