## 5) AI Agent Architecture (Structural)

### Agent Overview

- **Purpose:** safe, explainable automation across scheduling and visit support.
- **Design:** one orchestrated platform with specialized agent modules.

### Agent Roles

| Agent | Responsibility | Key Decisions |
|---|---|---|
| Intake & Intent Agent | Understand need and urgency | classify intent, choose workflow |
| Scheduling Optimization Agent | Recommend provider/slot options | ranking tradeoffs: time/continuity/distance/rules |
| Encounter Preparation Agent | Capture updates and generate summary | include/exclude context, highlight risks/questions |
| Engagement & Continuity Agent | Post-visit reminders, survey, follow-up prompts | timing/cadence/channel/re-engagement path |

### Structural Diagram (Mermaid)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Perception/Input Module] --> B[Planning + Policy Module]
    B --> C[Knowledge + Memory Module]
    C --> D[Tool Connector Module]
    D --> E[Action/Execution Module]

    D --> D1[Scheduling APIs]
    D --> D2[EHR APIs]
    D --> D3[Maps/Traffic APIs]
    D --> D4[Notification APIs]
    D --> D5[Analytics Store]
```

### Why This Architecture

- Separates policy/clinical risk logic from UI concerns.
- Supports asynchronous, scalable workflows.
- Improves auditability by module and decision point.
- Enables policy changes without deep rewrites.

